                    <item>
              <title>Teachmeets in Hampshire, Oxfordshire and Milton Keynes (South East)</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3679</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3679</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>Hi All</p>
<p>Has anyone seen about the Teachmeets that are happening  in the South East over the next few months?</p>
<p>For those of you  reading this who don't know what a teachmeet is, it is an informal  gathering that is organised by teachers for teachers to share real  classroom practice and to discuss ideas and themes.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Teachmeets  are free. There are presentation slots that can last between&nbsp; 2-7  minutes, but don't be put off by these presentations as the agreement  is...you are not allowed to be boring, no overkill with PowerPoint and  if you are a company you are not allowed to sell anything!&nbsp; If you are  not doing a presentation, you are still welcome to come along and be a  "lurker" - which means you can listen without having to participate!</p>
<p>There  is also plenty of time to talk to other colleagues to discuss things  like what you are currently doing in the classroom, what you would like  to be doing and how to do it.&nbsp; Basically it is an opportunity to share  ideas and information with fellow teachers.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The next teachmeet  (teachmeet Hampshire) is happening in Southampton on 20th May, then  there is one in Steventon, Oxfordshire (teachmeet fishbowl - focus is on  planning) on 17th June and then one in Milton Keynes on 7th July.&nbsp; If  you want further details, please visit  http://www.vital.ac.uk/community/course/view.php?id=289 MK one will be  put up as soon as we have confirmed all the details, so keep checking.</p>
<p>If  you've got any questions, please email me on  stephanie.young@vital.ac.uk, I'd be happy to hear from you!<img src="http://community.tes.co.uk/emoticons/emotion-2.gif" alt="Big Smile" /></p>
<p>See  you there!</p>
<p>Steph</p>]]></description>
