                    <item>
              <title>Developing confidence in evaluation</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/268</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/268</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[In classroom teaching, students can be hesitant to participate especially in demanding activities such as those requiring critical evaluation.

This sixth-form college course in ICT uses VLE activities as preparation for classroom work. For example, where students are asked to critically evaluate a web-based resources, they post their observations to a discussion board over several days. In class, their contributions are discussed and the tutor provides feedback. This has led to more participation, and more reflective and deeper contributions.

[Jackie Wilson]
]]></description>
          <pubDate>Mon, 28 Jul 2008 13:15:20 +0000</pubDate>
